 e\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: C
 hange in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usu
 al market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local 
 currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to consume
 r inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of
  inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Month
 ly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less 
 market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the m
 ain macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficia
 l source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-in
 flation/producer-price-indexes-australia/mar-2026\n\nExplainer:\n• Wha
 t it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received
  by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher
 -than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expe
 ct producer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why 
 traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure befo
 re it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly 
 in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\,
  but it can still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• 
 Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.ab
 s.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-i
 ndexes-australia/mar-2026\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price 
 Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods 
 and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can b
 e bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to
  flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can pr
 ovide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.
 \n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Not
 es: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter
  when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer
  Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/econ
 omy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia/mar-202
