 e\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n
 • Measures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: 
 Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency i
 f traders expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank po
 licy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and i
 s closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarter
 ly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for 
 consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI
  = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statisti
 cs/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-australia/mar-20
