  US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImp
 act: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nO
 fficial Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplaine
 r:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest
 -rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\
 n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually
  bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-
 expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bo
 nds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect int
 erest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.
 \n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The m
 arket often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the state
 ment\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Fe
 deral Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOffici
 al source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm\n\nEx
 plainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: In
 terest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central ba
 nk.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is u
 sually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish
 -than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish 
 for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affe
 ct interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk app
 etite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes:
  The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the
  statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOM
 C = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\n
 Official source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm
