 bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why t
 raders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicators because
  it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: 
 US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator releases an
 d quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items 
 such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying inflation p
 ressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source
 : https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/
 consumer-price-index-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consumer P
 rice Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumers for a
  basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-f
 orecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish 
 for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n• W
 hy traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicators bec
 ause it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequen
 cy: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator release
 s and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile it
 ems such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying inflati
 on pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial so
 urce: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflat
 ion/consumer-price-index-australia
