 s accelerating or slowing.\n\n• Frequency: Quarterly\, with revisions.
 \n\n• Notes: GDP can be backward-looking\, so markets often react more
  strongly when the result changes the outlook for central-bank policy or
  recession risk.\n\n• Acronyms: GDP = Gross Domestic Product.\n\nOffic
