 e Earnings\n\n• Measures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the lo
 cal currency if traders expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter c
 entral-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into i
 nflation and is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Mont
 hly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be
  positive for consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n•
  Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.g
 ov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202611\n\nExplainer:\n• What it
  is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Change in wage
 s and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast wage gr
 owth can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect stronger in
 flation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why traders car
 e: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely watched by central
  banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depending on release.\n\n
 • Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers but can also incre
 ase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOffi
 cial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202
