 eference period\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n
 • Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goo
 ds and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflat
 ion is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds\, be
 cause markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders car
 e: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicators because it can qu
 ickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is 
 monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quarterl
 y CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as fo
 od and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n
