 fficial Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC press conference entry.\n\
 nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures:
  Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central
  bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance i
 s usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dov
 ish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bulli
 sh for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly a
 ffect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk 
 appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Not
 es: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to 
 the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: 
 FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\
 n\nOfficial source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-decem
